This article is a transcript of a briefing by White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs. The briefing covers various topics, including the visit of French President Nicolas Sarkozy, financial regulatory reform, the Canada-Afghanistan relationship, the new nuclear disarmament treaty with Russia, rising right-wing extremism in the US, the President's upcoming trips, and immigration reform. Gibbs also discusses the President's views on Iran, health care reform, and the Black Farmers deadline.